name: Schulz Information Center- Sonoma State University Library
directions: Bottom floor of the library by taking a left after the Tech Help desk.  It is next to the Center for Community Engagement office and a statue of the Charlie Brown comics character, Woodstock.
comment: This is open for everyone to use. It is a single stall with ramp access and a small baby changing station. The sign says "gender neutral and family restroom."

name: Fabergé Restaurant

name: Claire's Corner Copia

name: WMU Sangren
directions: First floor of Sangren on the campus of WMU, by the other bathrooms near the vending machines.
comment: One-toilet bathroom. Designated as "unisex".

name: Hutchinson Hall
directions: It's on the floor of the building second from the top (across the hall from room 208). There's another one farther down the hall too.
comment: This is the drama building, and tends to be very safe for trans folks. Feel free to ask for directions, people are nice. If anyone bothers you, go into the undergraduate lounge (big green room) and tell someone if you need help, or just sit on a couch and wait it out.

name: Community High School
directions: On the first floor in the hallway with the NW entrance across from the Dance Body Studio
comment: Only for students/staff and approved visitors! Super big and handicap accessible with a lock. First gender neutral bathroom in an AAPS high school!!

name: Planned Parenthood - Ann Arbor Health Center
directions: The closest bathroom to the front entrance is straight pass the front desk to the left right before you hit the "staff only" door. The front desk staff is very friendly so feel free to ask them for the locations of all the bathrooms! Warning: There are often anti-choice protesters in the parking lot, but they're harmless.
comment: No need to be using any of PP's services to use the restroom! Planned Parenthood is very LGBTQ+ friendly, and they provide services for people who don't fit the gender binary!

name: Early to Bed adult and ftm supply store
directions: Straight back past the cashier
comment: Really queer friendly. Also a huge selection of basically ever packer and stand to pee device any Afab trans person could ever need. They even have packers for young children. Super friendly staff who are well educated on trans issues and they attend the philly trans health conference every year. It is an adult shop but it doesn't have any large piece of porn on display so you could whisk a child in and out without much trauma. Great place

name: Massey University - Wellington Campus
directions:
Room 7C55 - Block 7, Level C, Room 55.
Easiest access is through Finlay Terrace off Wallace St: Block 7 is the closest building to the stairs onto the campus you'll see on the left. Enter the door near those stairs down from Finlay Terrace, and keep going straight ahead through a series of fire doors.  Room 7C55 is in a small alcove roughly opposite Room 7C48.
comment:
Theoretically this room is accessible to university staff and students, but in practice anyone can use it because nobody can tell who is a student and who isn't. 
Accessible approximately 8am-6pm Monday to Friday, but be careful since the outer doors lock at 6pm and you need a keycard to get out. If you DO get stuck, don't panic: call security 0800 627750 and ask to be let out. Say you forgot your ID card, and are at the Finlay Terrace exit to Block 7.
